  { q: `Should I learn to read Japanese before visiting?`, a: `Learning hiragana and katakana (1-2 weeks each) is extremely helpful. Katakana lets you decode foreign loanwords on menus and signs. Many station names and restaurant menus include kana readings. Even without kanji, kana literacy opens up significantly more information.` },
